{"info": {"author": "David Cramer", "author_email": "dcramer@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Framework :: Pytest", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Software Development"], "description": "pytest-responses\n================\n\nAutomatically activate responses across your py.test-powered test suite (thus preventing HTTP requests).\n\n.. sourcecode:: shell\n\n    $ pip install pytest-responses\n\nIf particular tests need access to external domains, you can use the ``withoutresponses`` marker:\n\n.. sourcecode:: python\n\n    @pytest.mark.withoutresponses\n    def test_disabled():\n        with pytest.raises(ConnectionError):\n            requests.get('http://responses.invalid')\n\n        assert len(responses.calls) == 0\n\n\nAdditionally, you can use the responses fixture:\n\n.. sourcecode:: python\n\n    def test_enabled(responses):\n        with pytest.raises(ConnectionError):\n            requests.get('http://responses.invalid')\n\n        assert len(responses.calls) == 1\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/getsentry/pytest-responses", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache 2.0", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pytest-responses", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-responses/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-responses/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/getsentry/pytest-responses"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-responses/0.4.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "py.test integration for responses", "version": "0.4.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>Automatically activate responses across your py.test-powered test suite (thus preventing HTTP requests).</p>\n<pre>$ pip install pytest-responses\n</pre>\n<p>If particular tests need access to external domains, you can use the <tt>withoutresponses</tt> marker:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"nd\">@pytest</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mark</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">withoutresponses</span>\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">test_disabled</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">pytest</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">raises</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"ne\">ConnectionError</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">requests</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'http://responses.invalid'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n    <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"nb\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">responses</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">calls</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Additionally, you can use the responses fixture:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">test_enabled</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">responses</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">pytest</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">raises</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"ne\">ConnectionError</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">requests</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'http://responses.invalid'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n    <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"nb\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">responses</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">calls</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4756322, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5930738abfb3b1d1929a332c17d4a953", "sha256": "b6af7cabc5b5cb6b2db5d78da5266197fc551e759f0507054a831ab2851243a2"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest_responses-0.1.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5930738abfb3b1d1929a332c17d4a953", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "2.7", "requires_python": null, "size": 3418, "upload_time": "2016-12-12T21:11:28", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2016-12-12T21:11:28.271334Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/08/0e/87f1d1d858b1526f5de9346a4b00bcdac3cf33b777da3607c2e2c809371c/pytest_responses-0.1.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "d4b124be6271b99fc3b6e46439a699bf", "sha256": "5da8c20eea227137e5aeff6dba1243c7ac09ed1c3a01566e1441e1bd39cba44c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest-responses-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "d4b124be6271b99fc3b6e46439a699bf", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6020, "upload_time": "2016-12-12T21:11:26", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2016-12-12T21:11:26.232819Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/86/55/e45950fe6e7efc2924ed56b59ecad30d8d01386c9d6310b1582f7e717c63/pytest-responses-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.2.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "02deb9d2e7f4584c7bb1cc5edd1ca76f", "sha256": "13a342c11cbb4c11231403019cb1033a5e9f7917db5408f59c92806dc064e5eb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest_responses-0.2.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "02deb9d2e7f4584c7bb1cc5edd1ca76f", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "2.7", "requires_python": null, "size": 3545, "upload_time": "2017-07-25T20:11:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2017-07-25T20:11:07.026109Z", "url": "https://files